            .</p>
               <p>GEORGE JOSEPH FORD. I live in <placeName id="t18280110-217-crimeloc1140">Field-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-217-crimeloc1140" type="placeName" value="Field-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-217-crimeloc1140" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-217-off1138 t18280110-217-crimeloc1140"></join>. On the 5th of January, in the evening, I saw the prisoners pass my window two or three times, and told my shopman and apprentice to look after them; these boots were taken from the board at the window - I went out - found Stanton with them under his arm, and Haydon by his side; they were then going up a court into Holborn; I had seen the boots safe ten minutes before; Stanton said, "Let me go, it will be all right;" I took him, and my shopman took Haydon.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-217-person1295">
                  THOMAS 
                  LONG
               <interp inst="t18280110-217-person1295" type="surname" value="LONG"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-217-person1295" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-217-person1295" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I saw the prisoners go up Field-lane twice, between eight and nine o'clock in the evening, and the second time I heard an alarm that they had stolen the boots; I assisted in taking them to the watch-house; when I got up, Stanton had dropped one boot, and Mr. Ford was taking it up.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-217-person1296">
                  JOHN 
                  EDWARDS
               <interp inst="t18280110-217-person1296" type="surname" value="EDWARDS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-217-person1296" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-217-person1296" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I received the prisoners in charge at the watch-house; they said they were going to the play, but we found only a few halfpence on them.</p>
               <p>STANTON'S Defence. I had been cleaning a chimney which was on fire, and got intoxicated afterwards, and did not know what I was doing.</p>
               <p>HAYDON'S Defence. I know nothing about them.</p>
               <p>STANTON - <rs id="t18280110-217-verdict1141" type="verdictDescription">
